    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>sliced mushroom</strong> with 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[125ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min, with the lid on, or until they have softened</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion and mushrooms are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once softened, remove the lid and add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 8-10 min further, uncovered, stirring occasionally or until the onion and mushroom are caramelised</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta</strong> for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite, reboil a kettle</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, add your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> miso</strong></p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and cook for 1 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>cooked pasta</strong> with a splash of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>miso mushroom & caramelised onion bucatini</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jan-miso-mushroom-and-caramelised-onion-bucatini-with-broccoli-side/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>miso mushroom & caramelised onion bucatini</strong> and top with the <strong>salad</strong> and your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
